to succeed.

23:54.209 --> 23:56.084
Not havin' you and Kiki
out here

23:56.167 --> 23:58.250
is really wearin' me down.

23:58.334 --> 24:01.292
I don't know
if I can keep doin' it.

24:01.376 --> 24:05.167
It's like sometimes
I feel like I'm half a man
or somethin'.

24:05.250 --> 24:09.376
Oh, Mr. Greane.
You are a lot of things...

24:09.459 --> 24:12.167
but half a man
ain't one of 'em.

24:12.250 --> 24:13.834
That's a full man.

24:13.918 --> 24:15.584
( squeals, laughs )

24:15.668 --> 24:17.376
- Feel this full...
- ( phone chimes )

24:17.459 --> 24:19.084
man... of yours...

24:19.167 --> 24:20.709
- ( phone chimes )
- ...go to work.

24:20.793 --> 24:22.000
You see Andrew anywhere?

24:22.084 --> 24:23.459
Julie:
No. He wasn't out there.

24:23.542 --> 24:25.626
Charles:
OK, well, that's...

24:25.709 --> 24:27.584
Let's clear off
this desk...

24:27.668 --> 24:29.459
Radio commentator: ...another
incredible class of athletes

24:29.542 --> 24:31.793
- to look at again this year.
- ( phone chiming )

24:31.876 --> 24:33.459
Julian, what can I
do for you?

24:33.542 --> 24:35.876
The kid's incredible.

24:35.959 --> 24:37.542
He's once in a generation.

24:37.626 --> 24:40.250
I made it 250
to take it off the table.

24:40.334 --> 24:42.626
Smart move.
You won't regret it.

24:42.709 --> 24:45.334
- J, I gotta run.
- Hey--

24:46.959 --> 24:49.542
( siren bleats )

24:52.542 --> 24:54.084
( thunder rumbling )

25:06.584 --> 25:08.584
Evenin', Mr. Strasmore.

25:11.042 --> 25:12.876
( chuckles ) OK.

25:12.959 --> 25:14.668
Is there a problem,
Officer?

25:14.751 --> 25:16.918
Cop:
I sure hope not.

25:17.000 --> 25:19.417
You wanna step out
of the vehicle,
Mr. Strasmore?

25:19.501 --> 25:21.834
And why would I
want to do that?

25:21.918 --> 25:25.084
Because we asked you
so damn nice.

25:25.167 --> 25:27.250
( police dog panting )

25:28.834 --> 25:30.250
( dog barks )

25:30.334 --> 25:33.876
- ( dog growls )
- Spencer: Oh...

25:33.959 --> 25:36.042
so you think I'd bomb
my own plane, huh?

25:36.125 --> 25:38.376
That's Trigger.
He's not so much on bombs,

25:38.459 --> 25:40.334
but he likes him some drugs.

25:40.417 --> 25:42.501
By that, I mean
he likes findin' 'em.

25:42.584 --> 25:44.876
We've had a lot of problems
with private flights

25:44.959 --> 25:47.417
transportin' cash
and narcotics lately.

25:47.501 --> 25:50.042
We're just gonna take
a little peek in your rental
before you go.

25:50.125 --> 25:52.459
- Sure.
- ( dog barks, growls )

25:55.542 --> 25:57.125
( chuckling )

25:57.209 --> 25:58.876
I got a script for those.

25:58.959 --> 26:00.751
That's a lot of pills
for one man.

26:00.834 --> 26:03.542
That's enough
to get an elephant high.

26:03.626 --> 26:05.918
You know, sellin' those
is a felony.

26:07.334 --> 26:09.459
No shit.

26:09.542 --> 26:11.334
( door slams )

26:11.417 --> 26:12.959
( buzzer )

26:26.125 --> 26:30.167
Man: Mr. Strasmore.
I hear you have some...

26:30.250 --> 26:31.834
pill problems.

26:33.668 --> 26:36.584
- Lawyer.
- That won't be necessary,
Spencer.

26:36.668 --> 26:38.959
You don't mind
if I call you Spencer,
do you?

26:39.042 --> 26:40.042
Who are you?

26:40.125 --> 26:42.376
My name is
Jimmy Dale Pritchard,

26:42.459 --> 26:45.000
but my friends call me J.D.

26:45.084 --> 26:46.793
I got a script
for those pills, J.D.

26:46.876 --> 26:49.000
Oh, I don't care
about those pills.

26:49.084 --> 26:51.918
That was just my way
of gettin' the boys to be
able to bring you in

26:52.000 --> 26:54.209
so that we could
have a little chat.

26:54.292 --> 26:56.584
( laughs ) I know
it was a bit dramatic.

26:56.668 --> 27:00.501
But we wanted to make sure
that we had your...

27:00.584 --> 27:02.417
undivided attention.

27:02.501 --> 27:04.501
Who's "we"?

27:04.584 --> 27:06.834
Is this your first time
in Columbus?

27:06.918 --> 27:08.834
You know, this is
a beautiful city,

27:08.918 --> 27:10.668
and a great place
to go to school.

27:10.751 --> 27:13.084
You know, I met my wife
on campus?

27:13.167 --> 27:16.084
Thirty-five years ago.
And we still goin' strong.

27:16.167 --> 27:17.918
( chuckles ) Hey, now,

27:18.000 --> 27:20.959
you may find this
hard to believe, but...

27:21.042 --> 27:23.000
I used to play
a little bit myself.

27:23.084 --> 27:25.292
Yeah. I mean,
second string, of course.

27:25.376 --> 27:27.918
But, man,
did I have the spirit!

27:29.209 --> 27:33.959
You know the guy Todd
that you spoke to today?

27:34.042 --> 27:38.209
- He was my freshman roommate.
- Ah. So you're a booster.

27:39.918 --> 27:41.042
I hate that word.

27:42.209 --> 27:45.876
I prefer...
"enthusiastic supporter."

27:47.709 --> 27:50.668
You see, I do all of this
just for the pride of it.

27:50.751 --> 27:53.292
Now, for someone like yourself,
that might be challenging.

27:53.376 --> 27:57.834
But... for some of us,
well, that's enough.

27:57.918 --> 28:00.125
( smacks wall ) Let me
tell you something, J.D.

28:00.209 --> 28:02.834
I was only trying
to help my girlfriend's son
make some life decisions.

28:02.918 --> 28:05.209
Maybe that's hard
for you to believe,
but it's the truth.

28:05.292 --> 28:07.793
Let me tell you something else.
If I happen to piss on
your Rose Parade,

28:07.876 --> 28:09.626
then you better open up
a goddamn umbrella,

28:09.709 --> 28:11.417
because you sauntering
in here, and this,

28:11.501 --> 28:13.167
and all this bullshit,
doesn't scare me one bit.

28:13.250 --> 28:16.918
That's good.
It doesn't scare you.

28:17.000 --> 28:20.334
Well, I got some friends
over at the NCAA

28:20.417 --> 28:23.793
